The invention provides a method for improving the weldability of an LED (Light Emitting Diode) chip. The method comprises the following steps: sequentially forming a buffer layer, a Bragg reflector, a lower cladding layer, a luminescent layer and an upper cladding layer on a substrate from bottom to top by first epitaxial growth; performing ICP (Inductively Coupled Plasma) dry etching to form a partial doping and sudden change area on the upper cladding layer; forming an epitaxial window layer by second epitaxial growth; and evaporating Au/BeAu/Au and GeAu/Au to form an independent chip by a cutting way. According to the method, the partial doping and sudden change area is formed by an epitaxial way below an electrode, and the recombination of charge carriers can be reduced just below the electrode; meanwhile, a peripheral area of the Bragg reflector is oxidized to effectively improve the weldability of the LED.
